                                         JOHANNESBURG - An off-duty officer has shot and killed two people in City Deep in Johannesburg. It's understood there was an argument between the officer and a group of community members earlier on Tuesday. Officials say the constable then took out his gun and shot the pair and wounded two others who were rushed to the hospital. Police then responded to the shooting and upon arrival, the officer started shooting at his colleagues who retaliated. The off-duty officer was taken to hospital where he later succumbed to his wounds. The police's Mavela Masonda said: “As the police, we are investigating the circumstances surrounding an incident where an off-duty police officer allegedly shot and killed two community members.”